''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian ''hund'', Old Saxon ''hund'' (Dutch [[hond]]), Old High German ''[[hunt]]'' (German ''[[Hund]]''), Old Norse ''[[hundr]]'' (Swedish ''[[hund#Swedish|hund]]''), Gothic [[𐌷𐌿𐌽𐌳𐍃]] (hunds).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Vedic Sanskrit [[श्वा]], Greek [[κύων]], Latin ''[[canis]]'', Latvian ''[[suns]]'', Old Irish ''[[cú]]'' (Welsh ''[[ci]]'').

